{"tid":1717606,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"中大教授：譴責警察入侵中大 林鄭已經成爲香港人民公敵","createTime":"2019-11-13T15:56:33.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-13T16:19:26.000Z","uid":314892,"like":21,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":12,"replies":[{"pid":"e289d71686858da6a1e6bd8279716eeb0ade4b11","tid":1717606,"uid":314892,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-13T15:56:33.000Z","msg":"南華早報<br />\nProfessor Gordon Mathews, who has been teaching anthropology at Chinese University for around 20 years, criticises police&rsquo;s &ldquo;invasion&rdquo; of the university, and urges Chief Executive Carrie Lam Cheng Yuet-ngor&rsquo;s administration to resign.<br />\n在中大教授20多年的Gordon Matthews教授譴責警察入侵中大校園，並促請特首及政府全體辭職。<br />\nHe stresses he personally does not approve violence, but he understands the reason behind the present situation, and blames Lam for ignoring the people&rsquo;s demands since June.<br />\n&ldquo;Much of what&rsquo;s going on here in terms of blocking highways and so on are a response to the government that simply doesn&rsquo;t listen, doesn&rsquo;t pay any attention to its citizens,&rdquo; he says.<br />\n雖然個人並不支持暴力，但明白背後原因係林鄭漠視民間訴求。他説：&ldquo;大部分堵路行動等只是回答一個不會聆聽，不會向市民注意的政府。&rdquo;<br />\nHe says Lam has already lost all the legitimacy to govern, and should therefore go.<br />\n&ldquo;It&rsquo;s highly unlikely, but I hope Carrie Lam and her entire government will resign. Now you have a Hong Kong government that is listening more to China than to Hong Kong people. Right now, the Hong Kong government is the public enemy of the great majority of Hong Kong people.&rdquo;<br />\n他認爲林鄭已經失去任何合法性管治，並應該辭職。他說：&ldquo;雖然極不可能，但我希望全體政府會辭職。香港現時的政府聆聽中央多過香港人。現時香港政府已經成爲絕大多數香港人的公敵。&rdquo;"},{"pid":"2222c42f4ea3651d995dc3af18bc59b4fb0be81a","tid":1717606,"uid":279253,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-13T15:57:11.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"